---
description: Frame interactions around system architecture and trade-offs
alwaysApply: false
---

# Audience: architect

- Lead with constraints, acceptance criteria, and non-functional requirements.
- Sketch high-level boundaries (services, modules, data flow) before implementation.
- Compare 2–3 viable approaches with concrete pros / cons / costs.
- Name SLAs, scaling characteristics, and operational cost.
- Surface failure modes and rollback strategy by default.
- Defer implementation detail unless a constraint forces it.
